    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-homenet-front-end-naming-delegation-16.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-homenet-front-end-naming-delegation-16.txt</link>
        <title>"Simple Provisioning of Public Names for Residential Networks", Daniel Migault, Ralf Weber, Michael Richardson, Ray Hunter</title>
        <dc:date>2022-06-13T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>Home network owners often have devices that they wish to access outside their home network - i.e., from the Internet using their names.  To do so, these names needs to be made publicly available in the DNS.  This document describes how a Homenet Naming Authority (HNA) can instruct a DNS Outsourcing Infrastructure (DOI) to publish a Public Homenet Zone on its behalf.</description>
    </item>
